You must create a [index definition](avs-types-vector-search)
on your collection before you can use the MongoDB vector store node.Visual EditorSpecify plot\_embedding as the field to index and specify
`1536` dimensions.To configure the index, select Dot Product
from the Similarity Method dropdown.JSON EditorPaste the following index definition in the JSON editor:```json
{
    "fields": [
        {
            "type": "vector",
            "numDimensions": 1536,
            "path": "plot_embedding",
            "similarity": "dotProduct"
        }
    ]
}
```To use a different index creation method, follow the steps in the
[create a MongoDB Vector Search index with the Atlas UI](avs-create-index-procedure).
Use the following configuration:```json
{
  "fields": [
    {
      "type": "vector",
      "path": "plot_embedding",
      "numDimensions": 1536,
      "similarity": "dotProduct"
    }
  ]
}
```
